First, let's understand what $f_r(n)$ means. It's the maximum number such that if a graph $G$ on $n$ vertices has the property that every subgraph $H$ on $m$ vertices can be made to have chromatic number at most $r+1$ by removing at most $f_r(m)$ edges, then $G$ itself has chromatic number at most $r+1$.

